values: so i'm in san antonio in a medical study.  they took all my bath things, its contraband, got that tea tree oil in it you know.  watch out for that stuff. i managed to smuggle in my toothpaste.  totally badass right?  and i'm getting a little bored.  when everyone's sleeping in the fucking barracks seriously like 30 ladies to a room, and i forgot my headlamp, i'm computered out.  sorry livejournal. you're totally late 90's early 00's.  but other then a little cabin fever i'm happy as lark.  can't wait to go back to austin though for some reality time before i plunge into the study world again.  i get a snack at 21:12 fuck yeah gimme some puddin.  i would really love a beer.  thanks.

So we're leaving this week.  Got a bag full of work for herbal studies and a semi-full pack of clothes for the road.  headed south by south west.  ending up in northern california and then wherever.  Momma's finally got another full time job drivin her rig from here to there and there to here.

So we're almost on our way.  In a couple weeks when the farm job is over whitney and i are heading south then southwest.  not sure whether we're heading to texas first or just oklahoma and than california.  definitely staying in northern california for a month at the most.  checking into new orleans after that.  Camping out as often as we can, putting our earth skills to the test.  As long as we stay away from freezing for the winter I'm satisfied.  
I've been going through my own personal hell for the past month, my ma's in the midst of a nervous breakdown and I can only offer her my love and frustration.  I'm convinced this whole thing is based on her financial problems and inability to relate to those around her and I don't know what to say to her about that anymore.  Apparently I'm from another planet but her life in the suburbs is not worth slaving over.  My only wish is that she pack up all the things she can take in a little flatbed pickup and build a cabin in the woods.  maybe have a llama or two and start loving life.

sexual harassment in the workplace is not fun.  I don't enjoy it anyway.  I'll poor you a cup of coffee, hell I'll even get you some sugar and cream.  but i will not flirt with you and go along laughing at your sick little comments.  yeah, i guess that means i won't be fucking you either.  I don't talk to you or look at you or smile at you because I'm shy.  I know it's hard to believe but I just don't like you.  aghhh.  i want to maul somebody.  
"oh, you are wet?"
no i'm venting. fucker.
and all this means is it's time for a new job -or better yet- no job.
with deceivingly neglected lookin Joey next to me, I'm set.  If I  focus all my attention on her.  not a care in the world.

I can't work for a farm that doesn't exist.
sooo I wrote a resume, designed a garden, even trained joey dog a little.

missed the sunrise over downtown milwaukee friday morning, distracted by coffee after a long mild night.  friday was surprisingly sunny, put me in a great mood.  been losing track of time lately.  attempted to watch the sunrise saturday morning a top the reservoir with ben and nathan, it was cloudy and the sky just went from black to pink around the horizon to grey.  then as we were walking across it to leave i was distracted by my coat and hit my head on one of the old tennis court bars.  and it felt so good to no longer be 18.  
i've been ridiculously prone to bustin my shit up lately.
christmas with my ma's family was depressing.  she had made vague threats about what would happen if i let it slip that i had been traveling and not attending college.  apparently my life is horribly embarrassing to her.  though she disagrees with them as much as i do it still matters.  i'm a threat to her reputation as a successful mother?  i ask tom what the problem  really is, he says something like, "we're worried about you, women don't hitchhike, and definetly do not hop trains."  i gave him more credit than he deserved, thought he was more open-minded.  renegade.  so fucking typical.  a woman's place is in the kitchen and he'd much rather see me there.    
ahh yeah that makes me feel good too.
I need to get the hell out of here. again.  every time i pay a visit to mom i regress.

I miss ashland and all the great people there. 
There's a bonfire tonite.. somewhere.
gotta get there!  
it's been a while since i've sat around one.
Is it too much to ask for some drums?
maybe a fiddle or guitar?
I actually sat down and sewed today. oh yeah and a shower.
It was at least 60 all day, fuckin beautiful.

made it here, saturday night, 5pm
got a ride into town with Victor, he also bought us dinner at a thai place.  good eatin!
good drinkin.. i've met so many awesome people on the road.  it's really restored my 
faith in mankind.  All four of us managed to sneak into Walk the Line on friday night in
Columbia.  it was a pretty good movie, with all the romance and all.  eye catching. 
Ate too much popcorn.  life has been good. gonna go drink, find tobacco, water.. many 
awesome women here. learn cello.  we'll be here for a while.

still in columbia mizzooo.  want to get on moving south, head to kansas city than arkansas.
chris and chris want to stay until thursday to kick it with some friends comin in then.  ahh i 
just want to get on with it.  i've had enough.  there's good people here and all but damn, with 
these boys drama, i feel like getting the fuck outta here.  plus it's going to get cold.  tomorrow. 
i've been eating so much good food for free.  
its ridiculous.

I'm free.  well at the moment i'm slaving away at laundry and random shit.  the next two days consist of juggling fun time with organizing/preparation for taking off time.  
i accidentaly chowed down on some of my moms diabetic cookies. haha. anyone want to purchase some skis? maybe a laptop?  they're niiice.  you love spending money, c'mon do it.

some one needs to tell me. right now. right. now.
oh fuck.  i smell like a drunk bum.  my right hand it burned.dddddddd a lot.
someone feed me.
please.

right hand get better now.  i didn't mean to touch the wood stove.  aggghhhh it makes me want to vomit and cry.  food.  not books.  food. fooooood.  water thanks melissa water.  fuck i don't know what kind of pain killers those were but thanks jim.  
ooooo i need to do laundry because i'm an alcoholic.

other news, gathered some people together to watch She-Male Heaven and eat corn.  mom came up with tom and kicked it w/all of us.  played The Best Game Ever with them.  they enjoyed every minute of it.  i don't think i did too shabby on my ecology test.  slowly convincing myself that coming back next year = not for me.  or maybe i will come back and just sit in on classes and sleep in the straw bale house or something.  
comin into town!

tomorrow we'll be going out and collecting data for the sumac foliar flagging report.  
because we're that cool.

"oh man, i'm sorry, i really want to but i can't, i work all day tomorrow." 
i was so fuckin tempted to be like, "SURE OK LETS GO!" and see what happens.  but i'm a pussy.  is kayaking considered a date?  was that a sexual advance?  i don't know.  but he's too old.  even for me.

I have registered for classes, finally.  and they're gonna be fun.  found out that I got credit for bio ap, so i don't have to take that shit again, instead i'm takin ecology, it's all intimidating to me, but i only have five courses so it shouldn't be too bad. a seminar that all freshmen are required to take, chemistry, intro to peace studies, ecology, and native american storytelling.  woo. no class on tuesdays, and they all start after 10:30, except chem.  no english.  except intro to peace is full of essays and papers.  uhh college.  the more i think about it i don't know how i feel about it.

and i'm in my head. and i'm just beggin for her to push out the window screen and say, "hey, wanna go for a walk?"  i don't know what i'll be able to say to him when i see him.  you say you forgive, and you think you do.  but when the idea.. when it comes around again there's this uncertainty. i tell him and still he goes back to her.  fuck malicious bitches.  i'll break your nose you scheming cunt.
oh god i hope i see her this weekend. and i hope i'm shitfaced.

i'll be home friday. yeah. one more day. i can hold out.  i'm thinkin today's a good day for a shower.  man the pasta shit at lunch has left a queer feeling in my stomach.  did i mention they have starbucks coffee now.  what the fuck?  we're all such whores. and the majority don't know it. yet.  WEEEEEK END.
